# Stock Alert — Project Rules

## Project Identity

Stock Alert is a **multi-user SaaS** application for monitoring stock prices and sending Telegram alerts when price thresholds are crossed. Built with Laravel 11 + MySQL 8 + Telegram Bot SDK + Yahoo Finance v8 API.

- **Primary interface**: Telegram bot (webhook mode)
- **Secondary interface**: Web dashboard (React + Inertia + Tailwind, Iterasi 2)
- **Server**: Ubuntu (dea-geekom) with Apache/Nginx, PHP-FPM, MySQL
- **Public access**: Tailscale Funnel
- **This is a live SaaS** — any update must consider multi-user production conditions

## Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology |
|-------|-----------|
| Backend | Laravel 11 + PHP 8.2+ |
| Database | MySQL 8 (`stock_alert` database) |
| Stock API | Yahoo Finance v8 (direct HTTP via `Http::get()`) |
| Telegram | `irazasyed/telegram-bot-sdk` (webhook mode) |
| Queue | Database driver (MVP) → Redis + Horizon (when scaling) |
| Scheduler | Laravel Task Scheduling (1 cron entry) |
| Frontend | React 18 + Inertia.js + Tailwind CSS 3 + Chart.js |
| Auth | Telegram ID-based (no Laravel Breeze/Jetstream) |

## Core Architecture Rules

### Multi-User Data Isolation (CRITICAL)
- **EVERY query must scope by `user_id`** — never return data across users
- All tables have `user_id` foreign key — always use `where('user_id', $user->id)` or Eloquent relationships
- `ResolveTelegramUser` middleware resolves the Telegram user from webhook payload — never trust raw `telegram_id` without lookup

### Stock Price Fetching (CRITICAL)
- **Deduplicate before fetch**: `SELECT DISTINCT ticker FROM tracked_stocks WHERE active = 1` across ALL users, then fetch once per unique ticker
- Never loop per-user and fetch API per user — this kills scale
- Cache fetched prices in memory during a single scheduler run (fetch ticker once, evaluate alerts for all users tracking that ticker)
- Yahoo Finance endpoint: `GET https://query1.finance.yahoo.com/v8/finance/chart/{TICKER}?interval=1d&range=1d`

### Alert Engine (CRITICAL)
- **Cross-over logic** prevents duplicate alerts: alert triggers ONLY when price *crosses* the threshold (not when it's already on the other side)
  - `direction = 'bawah'`: trigger if `previousPrice > targetPrice >= currentPrice`
  - `direction = 'atas'`: trigger if `previousPrice < targetPrice <= currentPrice`
- After trigger, set `is_triggered = true` — user must re-enable alert manually
- Always log notifications to `notification_logs` (success or failure)

### Telegram Bot Rules
- Bot operates in **webhook mode** (not long-polling) — faster response
- Webhook endpoint: `POST /telegram/webhook` (excluded from CSRF middleware)
- Always acknowledge webhook within 1 second — dispatch heavy work to queue if needed
- Commands: `/start` (register), `/help`, `/track <ticker>`, `/untrack <ticker>`, `/watchlist`, `/alert <ticker> <harga> <atas/bawah>`, `/alerts`, `/cancela <id>`, `/price <ticker>`, `/stats`

## Database Access

### MySQL MCP (PREFERRED)
- **ALWAYS use MySQL MCP** for database inspection — it's read-only, safe, and faster than Tinker
- Database: connect to `stock_alert` (or whatever the active DB is)
- Use for: data exploration, counts, structure checks, debugging data issues

### Laravel Artisan
- Use for: migrations, cache clearing, queue management, scheduler testing
- Never use Tinker for simple data queries — use MCP instead

## Documentation Automation

After every significant code change, update the relevant docs:

### Architecture Changes → `docs/architecture.md`
- Document CURRENT state (not intended state)
- Update Mermaid diagrams if data flow changed
- Log decisions in `docs/decisions.md`

### Feature Development → `docs/todo.md`
- Update task status: `[ ]` → `[WIP]` → `[done]`
- Move completed items to "Recently Completed" with date
- Reference specific files, functions, error messages

### Bug Fixes → `MEMORY.md`
- Log issue and solution
- Include actionable learning, not just descriptions
- Format: `### [ID] [Title (YYYY-MM-DD)] ✅ STATUS`

### Regular Maintenance
- When `todo.md` gets cluttered: archive old items, move future ideas to `docs/backlog.md`
- Keep `MEMORY.md` under 500 lines — archive to `memory-YYYY-MM.md`

## Testing

### Multi-User Testing (always verify)
- [ ] Two users tracking same ticker — data isolated
- [ ] Two users with different alerts on same ticker — each gets their own notification
- [ ] `/watchlist` doesn't leak across users
- [ ] Rate limiting works: spam commands → throttled

### Scheduler Testing
- Run `php artisan stocks:fetch-prices` manually before trusting cron
- Verify `price_history` has new rows after fetch
- Verify only triggered alerts get notifications (check `notification_logs`)
- Verify `is_triggered` flag prevents duplicate alerts

### Telegram Bot Testing
- Test all commands via actual Telegram chat (or HTTP POST to webhook endpoint)
- Verify webhook responds within 1 second
- Test invalid ticker, missing parameters, unauthorized users

## Pre-Deployment Checklist
- [ ] `php artisan migrate --pretend` — validates migrations
- [ ] `php artisan stocks:fetch-prices` — test price fetch manually
- [ ] Scheduler registered in `routes/console.php`
- [ ] Server cron: `* * * * * cd /path && php artisan schedule:run >> /dev/null 2>&1`
- [ ] Telegram webhook set: `curl POST .../setWebhook?url=...`
- [ ] `.env` has: `TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN`, webhook URL, DB credentials
- [ ] `APP_DEBUG=false` in production

## Code Quality
- Use `php artisan pint` before commits
- Follow Laravel conventions: Service classes in `app/Services/`, Commands in `app/Console/Commands/`
- Keep controllers thin — business logic in Service classes
- Always use Eloquent relationships, not raw joins unless necessary

## Cross-Referencing
- Always read existing docs before adding new content
- Link related decisions, tasks, and architecture changes
- Update multiple files when changes affect multiple areas
- This app is LIVE — consider production impact before any change
